cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as lemmatization and language modeling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an encoder-decoder architecture for lemmatization and uses joint learning for language modeling. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a model for natural language processing tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for lemmatization. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a deep learning architecture for lemmatization and language modeling.
